# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker Compose overrides — read automatically from this repo root
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` and uncomment any values you want to
# override. The defaults in ``docker-compose.yml`` work out of the
# box for typical single-machine deployments — most users won't need
# this file at all.
#
# Edits to values in this file require ``docker compose up -d`` to
# take effect (not just ``docker compose restart`` or the in-UI
# Restart button — those reuse the container's create-time env).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host filesystem
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# UID the agent container runs as. Must match your host user's UID
# so the bind-mounted ./agent/data is writable from both sides. The
# default of 1000 matches the first user on Linux and Windows/WSL2;
# the first user on macOS gets 501; subsequent users on either OS
# get incremented IDs (1001, 502, ...). To set this to your actual
# UID without manually editing this file:
#     echo "HOST_UID=$(id -u)" > .env
# HOST_UID=1000

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Web search backend
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# In Docker, the web-search backend choice and credentials live here
# (not in agent/.env — compose's environment block overrides any
# run-from-source values still there).
#
# Bundled SearXNG: start it with ``--profile search``, set
# WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER=searxng below. The default SEARXNG_URL of
# http://searxng:8080 (the compose service hostname) works as-is.
#
# External SearXNG: don't start the profile. Set both
# WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER=searxng AND SEARXNG_URL=https://your-host.
#
# Brave / Tavily: set WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER and the corresponding
# API key. Don't start ``--profile search``.
#
# Disabled: leave WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER unset / empty.

# WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER must be set explicitly to enable web search.
# Values: "brave", "tavily", "searxng". Unset = disabled.
# WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER=

# Brave Search — https://brave.com/search/api/
# BRAVE_API_KEY=

# Tavily — https://tavily.com/
# TAVILY_API_KEY=

# SearXNG URL. Defaults to http://searxng:8080 (the bundled compose
# service). Set explicitly to point at an external instance.
# SEARXNG_URL=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# F5-TTS server
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Bundled F5-TTS: start it with ``--profile tts`` (requires NVIDIA
# GPU + CUDA 12.8). Default TTS_URL of tts-server:9998 (the compose
# service hostname) works as-is — no need to set TTS_URL.
#
# External TTS server: set TTS_URL=external-host:9998 below. Don't
# start the profile.
#
# Disabled: explicitly set TTS_URL= (empty value, no quotes needed).
# This silences the agent's reachability probe so the Settings UI
# doesn't show a permanent "unreachable" indicator. Leaving the
# value unset uses the default of tts-server:9998, which the agent
# will keep probing.

# TTS_URL=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Web client — agent WebSocket URL override
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The web-client container comes with the agent WebSocket URL baked
# into the JS bundle at build time. At container start, if
# SWARPIUS_WS_URL is set, the entrypoint sed-rewrites the bundle to
# this value — so the same image can serve multiple deployments
# without rebuilding.
#
# Leave unset for typical single-host setups: the browser derives
# the URL from window.location, which handles loopback and LAN
# access automatically. Set this only when the browser reaches the
# agent under a different hostname than it reaches the web client.
#
# Caveat: using this override requires removing ``read_only: true``
# from the swarpius-web-client service in docker-compose.yml so the
# in-place sed can write. See SECURITY.md → Container hardening.
#
# Running from source (non-Docker) doesn't use this — set VITE_WS_URL
# in web-client/.env and rebuild with ``npm run build`` instead.

# SWARPIUS_WS_URL=ws://192.168.1.50:8080/ws

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Network exposure (bind IPs and host ports)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each service published to the host binds to 127.0.0.1 (loopback)
# by default — only browsers on the same machine can reach them.
# To expose a service on the LAN (other devices on your network),
# set its BIND_IP to 0.0.0.0.
#
# IMPORTANT: the agent and web client have no authentication. A
# service on 0.0.0.0 is reachable by anyone who can reach the
# host — see SECURITY.md before opening anything beyond a
# trusted LAN.
#
# The PORT values are the host-side ports; the container-side
# ports are fixed in docker-compose.yml. Change a PORT only if
# the default collides with another service on your host.

# Agent WebSocket — chat traffic from the web client.
# SWARPIUS_BIND_IP=127.0.0.1
# SWARPIUS_PORT=8080

# Web client (served by nginx in the swarpius-web-client container).
# CLIENT_BIND_IP=127.0.0.1
# CLIENT_PORT=5173

# SearXNG (bundled, requires --profile search). Only published to
# the host so you can hit the SearXNG UI directly for debugging;
# the agent talks to it over the internal Docker network regardless.
# SEARXNG_BIND_IP=127.0.0.1
# SEARXNG_PORT=8888

# F5-TTS server (bundled, requires --profile tts). Only published
# for debugging — same as SearXNG, the agent reaches it via the
# internal Docker network.
# TTS_BIND_IP=127.0.0.1
# TTS_API_PORT=9998
